 in contrast to the\nequal-mass case, one of the mechanisms to dissipate angular momentum is now\nasymmetric, and leads to large kick velocities (up to a few $10^4\\,{\\rm km/s}$)\nwhich could produce wandering remnant boson stars. We also compare the\ngravitational wave signals predicted from boson star binaries with those from\nblack hole binaries, and comment on the detectability of the differences with\nground interferometers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 16 Jan 2022 18:42:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 16 Sep 2022 20:07:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-20"}
